# Idempotency Standards

This document defines standards for building idempotent data pipelines that produce correct results on retry.

---

## Core Principle

An operation is idempotent if executing it multiple times with the same input produces the same result as executing it once. For data pipelines, this means:

- Re-running a pipeline for the same date produces identical output
- Retrying a failed step does not create duplicate records
- Partial failures can be recovered by re-running from the beginning

---

## Write Patterns

### Idempotent Write Strategies

| Strategy | Description | Use When |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| Overwrite partition | Replace entire partition | Batch pipelines with date partitions |
| Upsert (MERGE) | Insert or update by key | Record-level updates |
| Delete + Insert | Remove then rewrite | When MERGE is not available |
| Staging table | Write to temp, swap atomically | Critical tables needing zero downtime |

### Overwrite Partition (Preferred for Batch)

```python
def write_partition(df, table: str, partition_date: str):
    """Overwrite a single partition -- idempotent by design."""
    target_path = f"{table}/date={partition_date}"

    # Delete existing partition
    delete_partition(target_path)

    # Write new data
    df.to_parquet(target_path)
```

### Upsert Pattern

```sql
MERGE INTO target_table AS target
USING staging_table AS source
ON target.id = source.id
WHEN MATCHED THEN UPDATE SET
    target.value = source.value,
    target.updated_at = source.updated_at
WHEN NOT MATCHED THEN INSERT (id, value, updated_at)
    VALUES (source.id, source.value, source.updated_at);
```

