## Deduplication

### At-Least-Once to Exactly-Once

When the source delivers at-least-once (e.g., Kafka without exactly-once), deduplicate in the pipeline:

```python
def deduplicate(df, key_columns: list[str], timestamp_column: str):
    """Keep the latest record for each key."""
    return (
        df.sort_values(timestamp_column)
        .drop_duplicates(subset=key_columns, keep="last")
    )
```

### Deduplication Key Requirements

- [ ] Every record has a natural or surrogate unique key
- [ ] Key is stable across retries (not based on processing time)
- [ ] Key is documented in the data contract

