## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-Pattern | Why It's Bad | Correct Approach |
|--------------|--------------|------------------|
| Append-only writes without dedup | Duplicates on retry | Overwrite partition or upsert |
| Using processing timestamp as key | Key changes on retry | Use source event timestamp |
| No checkpoint for multi-step | Must restart from scratch | Checkpoint after each step |
| INSERT without ON CONFLICT | Duplicate key errors | Use UPSERT or MERGE |
